{{Quote|Excellent, the bell, the book, and the...well, I feel like I should say Candle, but I'm not sure why. Maybe that would be a good name for this warhead. The Candle. Hmm...|[[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:JPRB">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Jabba's Palace : Ree-Yees|Tatooine}}</ref>}}
'''The Candle''' was a prototype [[Warhead/Legends|warhead]] that belonged to [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]. It was stolen by a group of [[Sand Splitters|Sand Splitter]] [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] along with a precious bell and a valuable book. One, or more, of Jabba's lackeys was sent to the Sand Splitter [[Sand Splitter Cave|hideout]] by [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]] to retrieve the items. The mission was a complete success, and upon their return, Ree-Yees named the warhead "The Candle" which he thought was a fitting name for that particular warhead.<ref name="SWG:JPRB" />

